AN ACT relating to governmental financial administration; establishing [certain]
conditions of the acceptance of an appropriation [;] under certain
circumstances; and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes various provisions relating to state financing and the process of
2 appropriation. (NRS 353.150-353.246) This bill requires an entity, as a condition of the
3 acceptance of [any] an appropriation of [public] state money, to agree to comply with certain
4 civil rights or employment laws that are applicable to the entity.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 353 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. As a condition of the acceptance of [any] an appropriation of [public]
4 state money, an entity must agree to comply with any civil rights or employment
5 laws applicable to the entity, including, without limitation, such laws that contain
6 protections against retaliation for employees who seek to enforce, administer or
7 otherwise promote compliance with the law.
8 2. The acceptance of [public] state money by an entity is deemed the
9 agreement by the entity to the conditions prescribed by subsection 1.
10 3. As used in this section [, “civil] :
11 (a) “Civil rights or employment laws” means any state or federal law which
12 prohibits discrimination because of race, creed, color, national origin, sex, sexual
13 orientation, gender identity or expression, age or disability. The term includes,
14 without limitation:
15 [(a)] (1) Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 42 U.S.C. §§ 2000e et seq.;
16 [(b)] (2) The Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1967, 29 U.S.C. §§
17 621-634;
18 [(c)] (3) The Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, 42 U.S.C. §§ 12101 et
19 seq.; and
20 [(d)] (4) NRS 613.310 to 613.4383, inclusive.

